This species resembles 

W. kuroashii

but can be distinguished from the latter by the following combination of character states: pleural carina of propodeum entirely present in both sexes (absent posteriorly in both sexes of 

W. kuroashii

); propodeum finely rugulose in both sexes (coriaceous in both sexes of 

W. kuroashii

); T I 1.4-1.5 
x
as long as maximum width in both sexes (1.1-1.25 in females, 1.14-1.26 in males of 

W. kuroashii

). This species also resembles a Korean species, 

W. pallidus

Balueva & Lee, 2016 (male is unknown), but can be distinguished by the following combination of character states in females: a large yellow median spot of face present (absent in 

W. pallidus

); antenna with 24-25 flagellomeres (22-23 in 

W. pallidus

); scutellum finely and sparsely punctate on coriaceous background (entirely coriaceous in 

W. pallidus

); propodeum finely rugulose (coriaceous in 

W. pallidus

).
